{
  "block": 1,
  "unit": 2,
  "type": "grammar",
  "unitTitle": "Unit 2: Past simple, past continuous, used to",
  "sections": [
    {
      "type": "theory",
      "title": "Past simple",
      "content": [
        {
          "subtitle": "Form",
          "rows": [
            {
              "label": "statement",
              "left": "I/you/he/she/it/we/they **played** ..."
            },
            {
              "label": "negative",
              "left": "I/you/he/she/it/we/they **did not (didn't) play** ..."
            },
            {
              "label": "question",
              "left": "**Did** I/you/he/she/it/we/they **play** ...?"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "subtitle": "Use",
          "items": [
            "Completed actions",
            "Repeated actions in the past",
            "General truths about the past",
            "Main events in a story"
          ]
        },
        {
          "subtitle": "Examples",
          "items": [
            "I **saw** the new James Bond film yesterday.",
            "I **went** to the theatre four times last month.",
            "Fifty years ago, people **didn't spend** as much on entertainment as they do today.",
            "Josh **pushed** the door open and **looked** inside the room."
          ]
        },
        {
          "subtitle": "Helpful hints",
          "items": [
            "yesterday",
            "last week/summer/year/etc",
            "in January/2001/etc",
            "an hour/a week/a year ago"
          ]
        },
        {
          "subtitle": "Watch out!",
          "notes": [
            "Some verbs have irregular past simple forms."
          ]
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "theory",
      "title": "Past continuous",
      "content": [
        {
          "subtitle": "Form",
          "rows": [
            {
              "label": "statement",
              "left": "I/he/she/it **was playing** ...",
              "right": "You/we/they **were playing** ..."
            },
            {
              "label": "negative",
              "left": "I/he/she/it **was not (wasn't) playing** ...",
              "right": "You/we/they **were not (weren't) playing** ..."
            },
            {
              "label": "question",
              "left": "**Was** I/he/she/it **playing** ...?",
              "right": "**Were** you/we/they **playing** ...?"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "subtitle": "Use",
          "items": [
            "Actions happening at a moment in the past",
            "Two actions in progress at the same time",
            "Background information in a story"
          ]
        },
        {
          "subtitle": "Examples",
          "items": [
            "At nine o'clock last night, I **was watching** TV.",
            "I **was reading** a book while you **were doing** the washing-up.",
            "It **was raining**, so Wendy decided to go to the cinema."
          ]
        },
        {
          "subtitle": "Helpful hints",
          "items": [
            "at that moment",
            "at one/two/etc o'clock",
            "while"
          ]
        },
        {
          "subtitle": "Watch out!",
          "notes": [
            "When one action in the past happens in the middle of another, use past simple and past continuous together: The phone **rang** while I **was watching** a DVD.",
            "Do not use the past continuous for regular or repeated actions in the past."
          ]
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "theory",
      "title": "used to",
      "content": [
        {
          "subtitle": "Form",
          "formula": "used to + bare infinitive",
          "rows": [
            {
              "label": "statement",
              "left": "I/you/he/she/it/we/they **used to** ..."
            },
            {
              "label": "negative",
              "left": "I/you/he/she/it/we/they **never used to** ... / **didn't use to** ..."
            },
            {
              "label": "question",
              "left": "**Did** I/you/he/she/it/we/they **use to** ...?"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "subtitle": "Use",
          "items": [
            "Distant past habits and states"
          ]
        },
        {
          "subtitle": "Example",
          "items": [
            "When I was four, I **used to** eat ice cream every day."
          ]
        }
      ]
    }
  ]
}
